T1  - Editor's Comments: Change, Development, And Challenge At Amr
AU  - Kilduff, Martin
Y1  - 2006/01/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2006.19379620
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2006.19379620
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 8
EP  - 9
VL  - 31
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses several changes made to the journal ?Academy of Management Review? in 2005. The periodical has been available as a Web-based journal since July 1, 2005, with all submissions, reviews and decision letters being handled online. The number of associate editors employed has been increased and the switch to new technology has been taken advantage of to better utilize their expertise in dealing with important tasks. The associate editors working under the new system are responsible for deciding whether papers are sufficiently developed to warrant formal review. The journal's book review section is noted for furthering the Academy's goal of enhancing theory development within the field.
AB  - The article discusses several changes made to the journal ?Academy of Management Review? in 2005. The periodical has been available as a Web-based journal since July 1, 2005, with all submissions, reviews and decision letters being handled online. The number of associate editors employed has been increased and the switch to new technology has been taken advantage of to better utilize their expertise in dealing with important tasks. The associate editors working under the new system are responsible for deciding whether papers are sufficiently developed to warrant formal review. The journal's book review section is noted for furthering the Academy's goal of enhancing theory development within the field.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2006.19379620
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2006.19379620
Y2  - 2026/04/24
